outputs.description: Ensuring enabling environment:National policies, legislation, strategies and plans with budgets adopted in line with internationalstandards for modeling innovative approaches and scaling up of evidence based high impact health interventions in MCH, nutritionand ECD.

System strengthening to deliver essential quality health services for mothers and young children:Availability of and access toessential quality evidence based interventions, skilled human resources and delivery systems for mothers' and children's healthcare ensured through innovative demonstration models and scale up plans.

Parental and community empowerment to ensure the best start in life for every girl and boy:Caregivers know the range and benefitof services available for antenatal, childbirth and young child survival, are empowered to provide stimulating and responsive carefor their children, and have access to and use preventive and curative care
description text

System strengthening to deliver support to vulnerable children in communities:By end of 2020, an operational framework for thedelivery of integrated social support services for vulnerable children is tried out and ready for use throughout the country
description text

Enhanced policy and monitoring for child rights realizationBy end of 2020, state institutions have strengthened participatorysystems to implement and monitor laws, national programmes and strategies including human rights

Prior-Year Commitments
Operational support for delivery of programme results
By 2014, the state addresses gaps  related to children’s legislation and rights and maintains national reporting function on the state of the children’s rights
By end-2020, the Government has national policy on inclusive education
By end 2018, a normative and operational framework for new forms of pre-school early learning  and development services isdeveloped and tried out in two selected locations.
Operational support to programme implementation
An expanded partnership alliance is engaged in promoting inclusive child rights agenda at all levels
By 2015 evidence based budget allocations for national plans are increased and equitable

By end 2017, school readiness standards including child-friendly measurement tools, pre-primary curriculum, and pre-services/in-service programmes for pre-school, primary and secondary school specialists are updated in line with international quality andinclusive education standards.
By end-2020, the Government has capacity to assess preschools/schools for safety.
